The Ms. contains only one text:
I) Mäṣḥafä gәṣṣawe, Lectionary for the first half of the year (fols. 5ra-200vc)
I-1) Daily scriptural readings for the first half of the year (fols. 5ra-154vb)
- Mäskäräm (1st month): fols. 5ra-8vc, 9ra-33ra 
- Ṭǝqǝmt (2nd month): fols. 33ra-52vc
- Ḫǝdar (3rd month): fols. 52vc-80rb
- Taḫśaś (4th month): fols. 80rb-106rc
- Ṭǝrr (5th month): fols. 106va-131rc
- Yäkkatit (6th month): fols 131rc-154vb
I-2) Scriptural readings for Sundays, with Psalms (for the first half of the year) (fols. 154va-200vc)
- Mäskäräm 1 to 8 (liturgical period called Yoḥannәs, “John the Forerunner”): fols. 154va-155vc;
- Mäskäräm 8 (Zäkaryas): fols. 155vc-156vb;
- Mäskäräm 9 to 15 (liturgical period called Fәre,“the Fruits”): fols. 156vb-158ra;
- Mäskäräm 16 (Ḥәnṣätä beta krәstiyan): fols. 158ra-159rb;
- Mäskäräm 16 to 25 (liturgical period called Mäsqäl, “the Cross”): fols. 159rb-161rc;
- Mäskäräm 26 to Ḫǝdar 5 (liturgical period called Ṣәge, “the Flowers”): fols. 161rc-167ra;
- Ḫǝdar 6 to Taḫśaś 7 (liturgical period called ʾAstämḥәro, “the Supplication”): fols. 167ra-173r;
- Sunday of the Preaching to the following Saturday (liturgical period called Sәbkät, “the Preaching”): fols. 173rc-174rc;
- The following Sunday to the following Saturday (liturgical period called Bәrhan, “the Light”): fols. 174rc-175rb;
- The following Sunday to Taḫśaś 27 (Nolawi “the Sheperd”): fols. 175rb-176ra;
- Taḫśaś 28 (Märʿawi “the Bridegroom”): fols. 176ra-177ra;
- Taḫśaś 29 to Ṭǝrr 10 (Nazrәt, Ḫәḍnät) (liturgical period called Lәdät, “the Nativity”): fols-177ra-177vc;
- The Eve of the Epiphany (Gähad) to the Sunday of the Encounter (Qäbbäla ṣom): fols. 177vc-197rb;
- Fast of Nineveh (Nänäwe): fols. 197rb-197vc;
- Fast of Heraclius (Ḥәrqal): fols. 197vc-198vc;
- Monday, beginning of the Lent: fols. 198vc-200ra;
- Friday, end of the Lent: fols. 200ra-200vc.
